  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Management Unit for an Applied Research Programme into High Volume Transport</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The high level objective of the PMU is to achieve cost-effective, efficient and timely delivery of the research and uptake, capacity building and knowledge management programmes for HVT. The contract split into two parts; Part 1, lasting 15 months, will involve procurement of a review of the literature and evidence available under the four identified research areas and will deliver a series of state of knowledge papers, that will be used to identify and prioritise what future primary research might be undertaken in Part 2 and its scope. A detailed research plan will be proposed for Part 2 based on outcomes from Part 1. Part 2 is expected to run for 4 years.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This high level objective aims to optimise design, operational and maintenance options for high volume road and rail passenger transport in Low Income Countries (LIC) considering strategic road and rail infrastructure links between cities, towns and regionally.</narrative>
  </description>
